I’m back 🖤 #explore #reels #beach #shower

I didn’t just disappear from social media for no reason. For the past few years I’ve been trying to drown my demons every day but damn they knew how to swim. I sunk to darker places than I’d even want my enemies to go. I became everything I hated and never wanted to be, a fxck up. I broke and fell deeper and deeper to a point I thought I’d never make it out alive.

There is light even in the darkest of times, if one only remembers to turn on the light. I’ve turned on the light, I’m finally sober and I can’t wait to show you that even if you lose everything you can make your way back to the top. I’m so sorry for letting you down but I’m excited for this next journey in my life to make things right. I really hope you come along with me.

Stay sober kids, it’s not worth it 🖤
#sober #motivation #reels

and I won. Here's how I did it:

1. Out of sight - First thing I did was remove any alcohol/mixers out of my apartment. I didn't have the discipline at the beginning to be around it so it had to be removed.

2. Friendships - Cut off all the wrong friends convincing me to go out when I shouldn't. I reworked the relationships with my real friends to where we did lunches not dinners, we hit the gym/church not bars, we talk business not girls.

3. Accountability - I posted on all my social medias (10+ million followers) that I was going sober. I wanted to do this so if I snuck out my audience may see me out and keep me accountable. But the main reason was that if I drank I'd let down the millions who look up to me & come to me for strength. I needed that extra motivation to stay in & pull it off.

4. Schedule - You've heard it before, nothing good happens after midnight. I try to go to bed by 8. I do this to avoid any FOMO and if I get a text to go out at 10 pm I'm already asleep or in PJ's.

5. Hobbies - Alcoholics biggest reasons for relapsing is the failure to replace your alcoholic tendencies with real, productive hobbies. I would party for 10 hours straight, I now don't and have all that time to just sit around? No, I had to hit the gym for more hours, I go on morning runs, I read books on overcoming sobriety & business, I've built some new businesses and I've focused more on content than ever. Focusing all that time on bettering my future.

6. Why - For those tempting weekend nights out you must have a why. My why was stopping because I was done making all my haters proud of me while making my family disappointed. Every person who hates me, every ex, every online troll who sees me getting drunk & fat was happy and I would make my mother cry with my decisions. I was done, I stopped to now make my family & friends proud to see what I'm doing, no more feeling like a complete failure. 

Put yourself first for 6 months and see the insane benefits you receive. You are better and more capable than you're giving yourself credit for. If you want to be the best stay sober kids 🫡 #sober #inspiration #highvalueman
